wp get shortlink "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
================================================================

NAME
----

wp get shortlink - Returns the Short Link to a post for use in

SYNOPSIS
--------

Returns the Short Link to a post for use in
[PHP](/Glossary#PHP "Glossary"). It does NOT display the short link.

USAGE
-----

`  <?php wp_get_shortlink(); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$id` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) A post or blog id.
    Default: Default is 0, which means the current post or blog.

 `$context` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Whether the id is a 'blog' id, 'post' id, or 'media'
    id. If 'post', the post\_type of the post is consulted. If 'query',
    the current query is consulted to determine the id and context.
    Default: Default is 'post'.

 `$allow_slugs` 
:   ([*bool*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Bool "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Whether to allow post slugs in the shortlink.
    Default: It is up to the plugin how and whether to honor this.

EXAMPLES
--------

Display the short link in plain text.

Short URL:
[http://example.com/?p=1234](http://example.com/?p=1234 "http://example.com/?p=1234")

`  Short URL: <?php echo wp_get_shortlink(); ?> `

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`wp_get_shortlink()` is located in `wp-includes/link-template.php`.

